      "content": "thanks. i've already checked the receiving logs and the audit trails, and everything seems to line up on the paperwork side. there aren't any manual adjustments or late entries that explain why we're consistently short by a few units every single time. it feels like stuff is just... vanishing. \n\ncould there be any other reason for these small, constant losses that wouldn't necessarily show up as a clear error in the system? like, is there a common pattern for this kind of \"shrinkage\" in electronics warehouses?",
      "source": "evaluator"
